<div id="review_2167962663" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2167962663" />
    <a title="Alaina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50620706-alaina"><img alt="Alaina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451325817p2/50620706.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2167962663?book_show_action=true">Oct 29, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alaina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alaina" href="/user/show/50620706-alaina">Alaina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50620706-alaina?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50620706-alaina?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50620706-alaina?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50620706-alaina?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2167962663" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17339707030702694925">In <i>London Bridges</i> Alex has to face two killers that he has yet to catch: the weasel and the wolf. The weasel, aka Geoffrey Shafer, is a vicious serial killer who has been targeting prostitutes. Then there&apos;s the Wolf, who is a mastermind and psychopath, from <i>The Big Bad Wolf</i>.<br/><br/>Of course this book delivers mighty good twists and turns that I honestly had no idea were coming. It was super interesting to see how Alex realized that the Wolf and the Weasel were working together - and that they were real</span>
  <span id="freeText17339707030702694925" style="display:none">In <i>London Bridges</i> Alex has to face two killers that he has yet to catch: the weasel and the wolf. The weasel, aka Geoffrey Shafer, is a vicious serial killer who has been targeting prostitutes. Then there's the Wolf, who is a mastermind and psychopath, from <i>The Big Bad Wolf</i>.<br /><br />Of course this book delivers mighty good twists and turns that I honestly had no idea were coming. It was super interesting to see how Alex realized that the Wolf and the Weasel were working together - and that they were really good at it.<br /><br />Some deaths really shocked me in this book because I kept telling myself - like no, they aren't going to die. Patterson said they were good friends or companions. It's all good. THEN WHAM. Death.<br /><br />I'm also pretty sure this book gave me lots of tiny heart attacks. I'm glad that I read this super creepy thriller book and I can't wait to dive into the next one. I just hope Alex will learn how to solve some cases earlier into the book - especially since he's been dealing with more than one person or case throughout most of the books.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17339707030702694925" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


