<span id="freeTextContainer3374148377628621947"><b>Alex Cross - book No. 10</b>: The big bad &apos;Wolf&apos; returns, picking up the &apos;Weasel&apos; from &apos;Pop Goes The Weasel&apos; on his way to overtly attacking the FBI, CIA and Homeland Security… in addition to the USA, UK, Germany, France and Israel as he appears to form a coalition between the Red Mafyia and Islamic Fundamentalism! Yep... despite always being a bit over the top, the series takes a &apos;shark jump&apos; with organised crime using international terrorism for revenge and financial gains. Somehow, Patterson stil</span>
  <span id="freeText3374148377628621947" style="display:none"><b>Alex Cross - book No. 10</b>: The big bad 'Wolf' returns, picking up the 'Weasel' from 'Pop Goes The Weasel' on his way to overtly attacking the FBI, CIA and Homeland Security… in addition to the USA, UK, Germany, France and Israel as he appears to form a coalition between the Red Mafyia and Islamic Fundamentalism! Yep... despite always being a bit over the top, the series takes a 'shark jump' with organised crime using international terrorism for revenge and financial gains. Somehow, Patterson still manages to make it a page turner as the readers wants to see how/if they capture the Weasel and unmask the Wolf! 4 out of 12</span>
